name: Miss Ada
notes: This mediterranean spot has been a favorite since Hallie and Kerry moved to the neighborhood. After one memorable meal in November of 2018, the staff lowered the lights and turned up Hamilton Leithauser + Rostam's A 1000 Times, and Kerry asked Hallie to marry him.

name: Do or Dive Bar
notes: Do or Dive is Rookie's favorite bar, and not just because it's the only bar that will let him hang out inside. Try the frozen coffee.

name: Speedy Romeo
notes: Technically it's St. Louis-style pizza, but we think it's some of the best in Brooklyn. Fans of HBO's Girls might recognize the space as Café Grumpy.

name: Pequeña
notes: This tiny, cash-only Mexican restaurant serves the best quesadillas in Brooklyn.

name: BierWax
notes: It's like drinking beer and listening to records at home, but with much better collections of beer and records.

name: Olde Brooklyn Bagel Shoppe
notes: Don't let the stupid spelling of 'shoppe' fool you — these are the best bagels in Brooklyn. Cash only.

name: Ample Hills Ice Cream
notes: Whether we get a warm weekend at the end of March or not, this ice cream is worth trying. This location is our go-to, but there's another one at 305 Nevins St, right by the wedding venue.
